which they have retreated.
The reviving air of night, the inspiriting
consciousness
of freedom after so long incarceration,
brought back at once to Bradshawe his wonted
energy
and hardihood of character; and when Bettys
provided him with a weapon to use in any
extremity
to which they might be reduced in accomplishing
